## Chronology (partial — begins p. 430)

*Selected entries from Lewis's timeline of Middle Eastern history:*

- **25 BCE** — Roman expedition to Arabia
- **c.30 CE** — Crucifixion of Jesus Christ
- **622** — Hijra of Muhammad; beginning of Islamic era
- **630** — Muhammad conquers Mecca
- **632** — Death of Muhammad; Abu Bakr becomes first Caliph
- **633-7** — Arabs conquer Syria and Mesopotamia
- **656** — Murder of Uthman; beginning of first civil war in Islam
- **661** — Murder of Ali; beginning of Umayyad dynasty
- **680** — Battle of Karbala
- **750** — Fall of Umayyads; accession of Abbasids
- **751** — Arabs defeat Chinese near Talas; Chinese POWs introduce
  paper-making to the Islamic world
- **762-3** — Foundation of Baghdad by al-Mansur
- **813-33** — Reign of al-Ma'mun; development of Arabic science and letters
- **833-42** — Reign of al-Mu'tasim; beginning of Turkish domination
- **869-83** — Revolt of black slaves in southern Iraq
- **945** — Buwayhids occupy Baghdad
- **969** — Fatimids conquer Egypt, found Cairo
- **1055** — Seljuks take Baghdad
- **1071** — Defeat of Byzantine armies at Manzikert; Seljuk expansion
  into Anatolia
- **1096** — Crusaders arrive in Near East
- **1099** — Crusaders take Jerusalem
- **1187** — Battle of Hattin; Saladin defeats Crusaders, recaptures Jerusalem
- **1220** — Mongols conquer eastern territories of the Caliphate
- **1258** — Mongols capture Baghdad
- **c.1290-1320** — Rise of Ottoman principalities in western Anatolia
- **1453** — Capture of Constantinople by Mehmed II

<!-- pp. 433-444 -->

## Chronology (continued) & Maps

### Chronology: Early Modern Period (1492–1809)

- **1492** — Christians take Granada; Jews expelled from Spain; Columbus sails west
- **1498** — **Vasco de Gama** sails to India via Cape of Good Hope;
  Arab pilot **Ibn Majid** guides him from Africa to India
- **1501** — **Shah Isma'il** founds **Safavid dynasty** in Iran;
  imposes **Shi'ism** as official religion of Persia
- **1514** — First Ottoman-Persian war
- **1516–17** — Ottomans conquer Syria and Egypt, destroy **Mamluk Sultanate**;
  Sharif of Mecca accepts Ottoman suzerainty
- **1520–66** — Reign of **Süleyman the Magnificent**
- **1521** — Ottomans take Belgrade
- **1522** — Ottomans conquer Rhodes
- **1526** — **Battle of Mohacs**
- **1529** — First Ottoman siege of Vienna
- **1534** — Ottoman capture of Baghdad; first Ottoman conquest of Iraq
- **1539** — Ottoman capture of Aden
- **1552** — Russians take Kazan
- **1555** — Ottoman-Persian war; **Peace of Amasya** between Ottoman Empire and Iran
- **1556** — Russians take Astrakhan
- **1557** — Construction of **Süleymaniye mosque** in Istanbul
- **1565** — Ottoman siege of Malta
- **1571** — **Battle of Lepanto**
- **1573** — Ottomans conquer Cyprus
- **1587–1629** — Reign of **Shah 'Abbas** in Iran
- **1589** — Ottoman-Persian treaty records Ottoman victory
- **1598** — **Isfahan** becomes capital of Persia

### Chronology: 17th–18th Century

- **1602–27** — Ottoman-Persian wars
- **1606** — **Treaty of Sitvatorok** (marks Ottoman concession to Habsburgs)
- **1607** — Ottomans driven from Persian territory
- **1612** — Construction of **Masjid-i Shah** in Isfahan
- **1630–38** — Ottoman-Persian wars
- **1631** — Insurrections in Egypt, Yemen, Lebanon
- **1639** — Final Ottoman conquest of Iraq
- **1683** — Second Ottoman siege of Vienna
- **1699** — **Treaty of Carlowitz** (major Ottoman territorial loss to Europe)
- **1726** — First **Turkish printing press** in Istanbul
- **1733** — Ottoman-Persian war
- **1736–47** — **Nader Shah** in Persia
- **1768–74** — Ottoman-Russian war
- **1774** — **Treaty of Küçük Kaynarca** (Russia gains rights in Ottoman Empire)
- **1783** — Russian annexation of Crimea
- **1789** — Accession of reforming Sultan **Selim III**
- **1794** — **Qajar dynasty** established in Persia
- **1795** — Qajar shah takes Tehran as capital
- **1798–1801** — **French occupation of Egypt** (Napoleon)
- **1800** — Russians annex Georgia
- **1803** — **Wahhabis** occupy Mecca and Medina;
  **Treaty of Gulistan**: Persia cedes Caucasian provinces to Russia
- **1803–12** — Insurrection in Serbia
- **1805** — **Muhammad 'Ali** becomes effective ruler of Egypt
- **1809** — Beginning of regular shipping service from India to Suez

### Chronology: 19th Century

- **1821–29** — **Greek War of Independence**
- **1826–28** — New Russo-Persian war; Persia cedes Armenia to Russia
- **1827** — Ottoman naval defeat at **Navarino**
- **1828** — First official newspaper published in Egypt
- **1830** — French invade Algeria
- **1831–32** — First official newspaper published in Istanbul
- **1839** — British take Aden; **reform edict of the Rose Chamber**
  (Tanzimat begins)
- **1844** — Ottoman currency reform on European model
- **1853–55** — **Crimean War**
- **1855** — Introduction of telegraph
- **1856** — **Congress of Paris**
- **1861** — Creation of autonomous Lebanon
- **1863** — Foundation of the **Ottoman Bank**
- **1869** — Opening of **Suez Canal**; foundation of University of Istanbul
- **1876** — Ottoman constitution proclaimed;
  ***Al-Ahram*** founded — first Arabic daily paper in Egypt
- **1876–78** — Ottoman war with Serbia, then Russia
- **1878** — Ottoman constitution suspended; **Treaty of San Stefano**;
  **Congress of Berlin**: independence of Serbia, Romania, Bulgaria;
  Austria-Hungary occupies Bosnia-Herzegovina;
  Russia occupies eastern provinces
- **1881** — French occupy Tunisia
- **1882** — British occupy Egypt
- **1894–96** — **Armenian revolts** and their suppression
- **1897** — Ottoman-Greek war
- **1906** — **Persian constitutional revolution**

### Chronology: 20th Century (to 1994)

- **1908** — **Young Turk revolution**; opening of **Hijaz railway**
- **1911** — Italians conquer Tripoli
- **1912** — First Balkan war
- **1913** — Second Balkan war
- **1914** — Ottoman alliance with Germany
- **1916** — **Arab revolt** in Hijaz; Sharif Husayn assumes title of king
- **1917** — British occupy Baghdad and Jerusalem;
  adoption of **Gregorian calendar** in Ottoman Empire
- **1918** — End of Ottoman rule in Arab lands
- **1919** — Greek landing in Izmir
- **1920** — Grand National Assembly in Ankara; beginning of **Turkish War
  of Independence**; Mandates established for Syria (French),
  Palestine and Iraq (British); **Ibn Saud** becomes Sultan of Najd
- **1922** — Armistice of Mudanya; Anglo-Egyptian treaty
- **1923** — **Treaty of Lausanne**
- **1924–26** — Ibn Saud's forces occupy Hijaz; adopts title of king
- **1925** — Accession of **Reza Shah**, first ruler of **Pahlavi dynasty**
- **1932** — Iraq becomes independent;
  **Ibn Saud** proclaims **Saudi Arabian Kingdom**
- **1936** — Anglo-Egyptian treaty recognizing independence of Egypt
- **1945** — **League of Arab States** formed
- **1946** — Jordan becomes independent
- **1948** — End of Palestine Mandate; **establishment of Israel**;
  first Arab-Israel war
- **1951** — Libya becomes independent
- **1952** — Military coup in Cairo; King Faruq abdicates
- **1953** — Egypt becomes a republic
- **1956** — Sudan, Tunisia, Morocco become independent;
  Egypt nationalizes **Suez Canal**; Israel-Egypt war;
  **Anglo-French expedition to Suez**
- **1957** — Tunisia becomes a republic
- **1958** — Formation of **United Arab Republic** (Egypt + Syria);
  civil war in Lebanon; revolution in Iraq (becomes republic)
- **1961** — Kuwait becomes independent; Syria secedes from UAR
- **1962** — Slavery abolished in Yemen and Saudi Arabia
- **1967** — **Israel-Arab war** (Six-Day War); South Yemen becomes independent
- **1969** — Libya becomes a republic
- **1970** — Death of **Nasser**; **Sadat** succeeds
- **1971** — Gulf states become independent; formation of **Union of Arab Emirates**
- **1973** — **Arab-Israel war** (Yom Kippur)
- **1975–77** — Civil war in Lebanon
- **1979** — Egypt and Israel sign **peace treaty**; **Revolution in Iran**
- **1980–88** — **Iran-Iraq war**
- **1981** — Murder of **Anwar Sadat**
- **1982** — Israeli invasion of Lebanon
- **1990–91** — Iraq invades Kuwait; **Gulf War**
- **1994** — **Jordan-Israel peace treaty**

